data.text:
Emeka Okafor - Points

Emeka Okafor scores a career high 30 points (2005)

On March 12, 2005, Emeka Okafor set his career high in points in a NBA game. That day he scored 30 points in Charlotte's home loss against LA Lakers, 116-117. He also had 11 rebounds, 2 assists, 1 steal and 2 blocks. He shot 13/22 from two, shooting at 59.1% from the field. He also shot 4/6 from the free-throw line.

Emeka Okafor - Rebounds

Emeka Okafor grabs a career high 25 rebounds (2006)

On December 29, 2006, Emeka Okafor set his career high in rebounds in a NBA game. That day he grabbed 25 rebounds in Charlotte's home win against LA Lakers, 133-124. He also had 22 points and 4 blocks.

Emeka Okafor - Assists

Emeka Okafor gives a career high 5 assists (2007)

On April 14, 2007, Emeka Okafor tied his career high in assists in a NBA game. That day he dished 5 assists in Charlotte's road win against Milwaukee, 92-113. He also had 10 points, 5 rebounds and 2 blocks.

Emeka Okafor - Steals

Emeka Okafor has a career high 5 steals (2006)

On November 15, 2006, Emeka Okafor tied his career high in steals in a NBA game. That day he reached 5 steals in Charlotte's road win against San Antonio, 92-95. He also had 19 points, 9 rebounds and 1 assist.

Emeka Okafor - Blocks

Emeka Okafor blocks a career high 10 shots (2007)

On January 12, 2007, Emeka Okafor tied his career high in blocks in a NBA game. That day he went for 10 blocks in Charlotte's road win against New York, 110-126. He also had 20 points, 9 rebounds and 1 assist.
